title: Failed to start quarkus:dev with Quarkus V2.2.1
body:
### Describe the bug

When trying to start a Quarkus 2.2.1 application in dev-mode (using mvn quarkus:dev) I get the following error printed to the console and the application fails to start:

`[ERROR] Failed to execute goal io.quarkus:quarkus-maven-plugin:2.2.1.Final:dev (default-cli) on project adam-service: Execution default-cli of goal io.quarkus:quarkus-maven-plugin:2.2.1.Final:dev failed: A required class was missing while executing io.quarkus:quar
kus-maven-plugin:2.2.1.Final:dev: Could not initialize class org.fusesource.jansi.internal.Kernel32
[ERROR] -----------------------------------------------------
[ERROR] realm =    plugin>io.quarkus:quarkus-maven-plugin:2.2.1.Final-464092647
[ERROR] strategy = org.codehaus.plexus.classworlds.strategy.SelfFirstStrategy
...
`
This was reported as fixed in [19673](https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/issues/19673)

But it still fails.


### Expected behavior

Dev-mode should work

### Actual behavior

Quarkus does not start.

### How to Reproduce?

mvnw quarkus:dev

### Output of `uname -a` or `ver`

Microsoft Windows [Version 10.0.18363.1766]

### Output of `java -version`

openjdk version "11.0.10" 2021-01-19 LTS OpenJDK Runtime Environment Zulu11.45+27-CA (build 11.0.10+9-LTS) OpenJDK 64-Bit Server VM Zulu11.45+27-CA (build 11.0.10+9-LTS, mixed mode)

### GraalVM version (if different from Java)

_No response_

### Quarkus version or git rev

2.2.1

### Build tool (ie. output of `mvnw --version` or `gradlew --version`)

mvnw : Apache Maven 3.8.1

### Additional information

Dependency tree:
